# Syncthing-Sidecar-Binaries werden jetzt mit dem Repo committed (~28 MB pro
# Target, zusammen 56 MB — unter git's 100 MB Limit). Grund: GitHub Releases
# CDN ist zu unzuverlässig für CI (persistent 504 in v0.1.1/v0.1.2 builds).
# fetch-syncthing.sh bleibt als manuelles Refresh-Tool für Version-Updates.

# Rust build artifacts (also covered by src-tauri/.gitignore, listed here for clarity)
src-tauri/target

# Tauri Updater signing keys — private key MUST NOT be committed.
# Public .pub is in tauri.conf.json (safe to commit), but the raw .pub file
# is excluded for cleanliness.
syncomat-updater.key
syncomat-updater.key.pub

# Wiki-Snapshot (generiert via /wiki-snapshot, gepushed an wiki.ca-se.ch — kein Repo-Asset)
wiki-snapshot.md
